Iranian students are ready to die for their country's nuclear program.
They created a human shield
A few hundred high school students have created a human shield around a nuclear site in Iran.
They want to support their country's nuclear programme in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
Students began to pray at noon in front of the site and then wished for the death of the US and Israel.
A few hundred students from Ispahan universities created a human shield on Tuesday around the Ispahan Nuclear Technology Centre where uranium is transformed.
They have thus openly stated that they would defend their country's nuclear programme at the risk of their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) noted in its latest information that Iran has continued to strengthen its nuclear weapons.
Israel is reported to have a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
Students began to pray at noon in front of the site and then wished for the death of the US and Israel.
In the case of an attack, the objective of which would be to destroy the Iranian nuclear programme, the targets would be not only Ispahan, but also the Natanz site where uranium is enriched.
The diet of an obese child: do not take breakfast and take charcuterie for dinner
More than one third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren are overweight and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families with unhealthy lifestyles.
This again shows how important the environment in which the human being evolves and the models around him is.
For example, in the tables of obese children, there is 50% more charcuterie than in normal weight children's families.
19% of the obese had fries at dinner according to the survey conducted with an awareness action "Obesity is not a chance"
In the families of the big children sport is also not a habit, which is now the case with most of the students today - only 15% said that at least once a week parents found time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place in the last school year and involved 900 pupils from primary schools in Chechnya.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not a chance", action supported by General Health Insurance and Unilever Society.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students from sixth to third have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that causes a dramatic increase in the number of overweight and even obese children is the absence of a proper diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast-in case - lunch - snack-dining, which is a basic principle of a good diet," says one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast and charcuterie at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that having a healthy development requires some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In Chechnya, only 23% of students' families eat at the same time.
In most families each takes breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that's been raised is that a tenth of the population doesn't take breakfast at all.
Breakfast is, however, the basis for a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in obese children's families, unhealthy fries are more often consumed.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sweet drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children questioned do sports regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Get your food ready.
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food based on the possibilities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Among their favorite dishes there are many cakes, meats and sweets.
"The most alarming is in particular a high preference for sweet lemonades", is indicated in the results of the survey.
For lunch it is the pasta that took the first place right in front of the white meat.
Children did not want any starches at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Health focus
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the moment they receive the ad hoc information.
"During a review of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session "Obesity is not a chance", a determined will was observed to move towards a healthy diet," the survey results indicate.
For example, the most notable was sweet lemonade since children began to give preference to drinking water.
The children most often checked the questionnaire for white meat and fish as a main dish and would reduce sweet dishes and knedliky (Czech speciality of breadmeal balls or potatoes).
