The need for speed The Run is fighting all over America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with a routine morning shift at work.
This fills everyone's ambition to some extent, but it's useless if no one wants to do anything else.
The new subtitled The Run produced great expectations before it was released.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed racing series and to come out a kind of game from the playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be in which the main hero comes out of his car and does what he wants.
As already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was achieved.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole shoots down because of some useless mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of an incomprehensible phainetosis on the part of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them starts to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to get the first one to New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on another route and the stages planned in different environments that are quite distinct from each other and interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a single moment that the game proposes something identical to him.
Some environments are quite nice overcroit even though the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
Well, that's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition to time with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you must be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Next to this the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a few, but that's enough.
A few moments ago you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) and then you run against the watch (classic duel with the timer) and then another duel awaits you with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and who try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle crossings.
It's more of an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away to someone and you have to help him by typing on the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer times of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is as good as this because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that accommodate the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means there's nothing extraordinary right now, but we can't say it's negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to go to another place.
But although we can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
At the difference of the driving model, the collision model is not yet at the point.
We do not expect from this game a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you do not have, in a collision with any object, any idea of how your car behaves, it is therefore not completely good.
During tight exceedances you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car leaves in crazy voltigos.
Or it's in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done so that when you broke the figure or you went out into the decor the game brings you back to the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you must start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more a tool, in case something doesn't happen the right way, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and you have to find the solution by remembering from memory the piece of itinerary in question.
The big thing about this game is that the same actions are in the same places.
For example, there are some turns that need to be passed in a certain way or that does not happen.
Otherwise you meet in a given place "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute late.
What gets angry are the situations when you see easily passing the opponent between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you either have to put yourself aside and bypass them or brake them.
It's equal if you go ahead of him because it's "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always comes close to your nose.
The opponents still have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you to the same place.
This gets the most angry at the end of the game when you roll on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at all costs pass in front of you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you come into collision a lot of times.
We can understand that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it's equal if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or something else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You need to pay attention to gasoline pumps on the routes because you can change cars there however most of the time you have enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American cylinders for straight motorways and super sports cars with exotic twists on very technical pipes, for example on lancet roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places you know about adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This one connects online with the Autolog function which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult blows to understand is the situation of the last race of adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator shows you between 150 and 200 km/hour (previously) and behind you comes a subway train that sends you the car directly to the ferry.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought when creating this game or whether the authors really think of us as fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is disturbing is that in more extreme situations imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This mainly concerns accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer used for anything.
The sound part is good and the track is the choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the youngest public a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confusing.
If the game didn't have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it's the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it's not over.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself for the faults to hit you in the eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from higher schools and secondary schools.
The clove of the festival consists of two concerts organized on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the Rector Vaclav Hampl", says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The clove of the festival is the concert of the Choeur des lécoles et classes secondaryes which takes place with free entry on 17 November from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Jazz Mass Celebration.
In the evening the concert "Students of velvet" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady where the choirs of the higher schools and that of Charles University take place.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and recall the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Czech Cherry Union in cooperation with Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from November 16 to 20 in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Participants will find all information on the internet pages of the festival www.festaaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
"I didn't expect such a hard war."
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role," said Milena Vicenova, Czech Ambassador to the European Union, who began her presentation at the Faculty of Law.
When she was able to describe the different bodies of the EU and their relations in such an understandable and visible way that a large number of speakers at Charles University's Faculty of Law could envy her, she showed how much she took her motto "understandable and openly about Europe" very seriously.
Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning the criticisms echoed that he is tired, that it is a round-of-leather, that he cannot replenish any mission and I have to say that he has cut everyone's breath because he holds his role to perfection."
"He is a man who can listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to be taken from Europe."
She explained the new position of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy in the context of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "What telephone number should I call?", therefore as an important step towards the unity and greater legibility of the Union's policy vis-à-vis the states, such as China or India.
No one wants to ban our syrecky (cooked pasta cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has experienced, lives and will live in a short time.
She called the Czech presidency a success two years ago.
The Czechs resolved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or organized a Summit for an Eastern Partnership.
It described the fall of the government as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
According to the words of the Ambassador, "the activity has beaten its full" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved now.
It is also necessary to approve the new septimal budget of the Union, which is becoming very complicated because of the current economic situation.
As it would appear that the budget will be thin and for savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped most, at least, everything is to be resolved in the context of future negotiations.
Madam Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an comprehensible Europe".
"I really don't like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted horns, bananas that are different large or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky."
It wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador the Czechs have the reputation of being eurosceptics and people who only see things in their negative aspect more than positively.
Furthermore, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
According to her, the fault results from several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a letter of motivation and weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech Presidency, she then stressed the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Polish, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman tells me: 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?" and he is not at all happy."
According to Mrs Vicenova, in the near future it is new hard rules on budgetary policy that await the Member States.
It is the concept of a two-speed Europe, if not a multi-speed Europe, that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
"We have countries in the euro area and others outside the area."
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the strengthened cooperation institute".
First of all, it was said that the countries that want to cooperate with each other and those that do not want to cooperate remain in their own corner."
"There will be many such institutes and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," says Vicenova.
From this point of view, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all themes having an impact on the EU must be discussed among all EU members and not just the Eurozone members.
