The foundation of this long-term strategy was laid by the company's first head, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved in the near future so that people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE'!" became the imprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to edit in 1935).
It was the foundation of the culture of the company carefully developed by Watson.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it always remained faithful to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more"a delay for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to take care of his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - the people of IBM were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacations, an insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and commmercials.
Similarly, IBM has a well-developed client relationship system.
The company was at the beginning great in the discovery of talents- as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and could thus have the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman- Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been working at IBM for 30 years and is currently in the position of Chief of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has been doing what is called jamy, brainstorming online from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
It is no wonder that there are many ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
