It will be recalled that Michoacán did not approve his Political Constitution, the Electoral Code of State or the Electoral Justice Act, while the Congress of the State approved the reforms shortly before the end of the legal period for this electoral trial to come into force and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel failed to publish it within the time limits provided for in the Law of the Official Journal of the State, with the argument that he had some objections.
On the same 9 November, the Supreme Court of Justice of the Nation (SCJN) resolved the constitutional controversy promoted by the local legislature and called it "invalid and illegal" the vote of the state's representative for constitutional reforms, because he does not have the right to "sanction or challenge them".
Interviewed on the possibility of "vote by vote", María de los Ángeles Llanderal said that thanks to the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of IEM it will be possible to carry out the partial and total counts of votes by the local electoral body.
Thus, the partial counting of votes, one or more electoral packages, it may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no record of voting and counting in the ballot paper is not found in the president of the ballot; or there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total count of votes received in all ballot boxes may be made when there is an indication that the difference between the supposed candidate winning the respective election and the candidate who obtained the second place in the election is equal to or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition from the party representative and/or coalition who presented the second of the candidates reported.
The total counting of the ballot may also be achieved if, at the end of the joint counting, it results that the difference between the candidate presumed to be winning and the candidate of the second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is an express petition from the representative of the political party whose candidate has emerged second, in which case electoral packages which have been the subject of the partial counting will be excluded.
It should be mentioned that this is the situation of the election of Morelia, where according to the PRSP, the difference between the first and second places is only 0.16 percent, even without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total minutes.
