The Italian company Modo Modo, based in Milan, decided at the time to launch a design notebook but distinguished.
Maria Sebregondi, then consultant for the company, is responsible for launching the new product.
The notebook is inspired by an old production technique, the mole skin (tupee skin) which means a varnished cotton used to cover banquets, for example.
